math

Class Tensor

  • java.lang.Object
    • math.Tensor

  • public class Tensor
extends java.lang.Object
    A Tensor represents a n-dimensional matrix of a given node. It can be passed to any node and broadcasted to the expected shape.

    • Method Detail

      • broadcast

        public static Tensor[] broadcast(Tensor... tensors)
        Broadcasts the given tensors. This alters the tensors such that their shapes are compatible. The dimensions are iterated starting from the number of columns, and are broadcast if the dimensions match, or one dimension equals zero.
        Parameters:
        tensors - the tensors to broadcast
        Returns:
        an array of broadcast tensors
